WEBVTT

00:00:00.480 --> 00:00:05.760
<v Speaker 1>What was to follow or to continue to carry on?

00:00:05.840 --> 00:00:06.800
<v Speaker 1>Seguir.

00:00:06.800 --> 00:00:07.600
<v Speaker 1>Seguir.

00:00:07.600 --> 00:00:11.920
<v Speaker 1>And how was I continue or I carry on or I follow?

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:13.960
<v Speaker 1>Sego.

00:00:13.960 --> 00:00:15.480
<v Speaker 1>Sego, good.

00:00:15.480 --> 00:00:21.320
<v Speaker 1>If you want to say I continue speaking, here we use the ing.

00:00:21.320 --> 00:00:23.160
<v Speaker 1>I continue speaking.

00:00:23.160 --> 00:00:24.920
<v Speaker 1>So how would that be?

00:00:26.160 --> 00:00:27.920
<v Speaker 2>Sigo hablando.

00:00:27.920 --> 00:00:29.440
<v Speaker 1>Sigo hablando.

00:00:29.440 --> 00:00:32.000
<v Speaker 1>He continues speaking.

00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:34.000
<v Speaker 2>Sigue hablando.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:35.280
<v Speaker 1>Sigue hablando.

00:00:35.280 --> 00:00:36.560
<v Speaker 1>He continues speaking.

00:00:36.560 --> 00:00:37.600
<v Speaker 1>She continues speaking.

00:00:37.600 --> 00:00:40.000
<v Speaker 1>You formal continue speaking.

00:00:40.360 --> 00:00:43.720
<v Speaker 1>It's probable that he continues speaking.

00:00:43.720 --> 00:00:52.360
<v Speaker 1>So in English we will probably say he'll probably continue speaking, but in Spanish it is probable that he continues speaking.

00:00:52.360 --> 00:00:54.760
<v Speaker 1>So how would that be?

00:00:58.860 --> 00:00:59.980
<v Speaker 1>Very good.

00:01:02.620 --> 00:01:05.660
<v Speaker 1>It's probable that he continues speaking.

00:01:05.460 --> 00:01:11.540
<v Speaker 1>So after Segir, to get the meaning of continue, we can use the ing.

00:01:11.540 --> 00:01:15.300
<v Speaker 1>What was to be for characteristics?

