<v Speaker 1>How would you make the ing form of ser?

00:01:22.299 --> 00:01:23.259
<v Speaker 2>Siento.

00:01:23.259 --> 00:01:24.299
<v Speaker 1>Siendo.

00:01:24.299 --> 00:01:30.060
<v Speaker 1>Free in the sense of not requiring any money is gratis in Spanish.

00:01:30.020 --> 00:01:30.820
<v Speaker 1>Gratis.

00:01:30.820 --> 00:01:33.780
<v Speaker 1>This is where we get gratuitous from in English.

00:01:33.780 --> 00:01:35.219
<v Speaker 1>It's a bit gratuitous.

00:01:35.219 --> 00:01:36.259
<v Speaker 1>It's unnecessary.

00:01:36.259 --> 00:01:36.820
<v Speaker 1>It's free.

00:01:36.820 --> 00:01:37.939
<v Speaker 1>It's extra.

00:01:37.939 --> 00:01:39.299
<v Speaker 1>Gratis.

00:01:38.920 --> 00:01:43.080
<v Speaker 1>So you can say it's imperative that it continues to be free.

00:01:43.080 --> 00:01:45.880
<v Speaker 1>So it's imperative that it continues being free.

00:01:45.880 --> 00:01:47.799
<v Speaker 1>How would you say that?

00:01:53.539 --> 00:01:54.180
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:01:54.180 --> 00:01:58.259
<v Speaker 1>It's imperative that siga siendo gratis.

00:01:58.460 --> 00:02:04.620
<v Speaker 1>To start, we said that we had comensar and empezar.

00:02:04.620 --> 00:02:09.340
<v Speaker 1>Comenzar is of course easier to remember and use because it sounds like commence.

00:02:09.040 --> 00:02:13.120
<v Speaker 1>But M Pesar is probably more common.

00:02:13.120 --> 00:02:15.920
<v Speaker 1>So you can use whichever you like now.

00:02:15.920 --> 00:02:19.600
<v Speaker 1>How would you say it's spectacular that

00:02:20.180 --> 00:02:22.739
<v Speaker 1>They start to speak Spanish.

00:02:22.739 --> 00:02:27.540
<v Speaker 1>Now after start to connect to the next two forms you need a

