<v Speaker 1>Spectacular is the same word in Spanish

00:02:57.980 --> 00:03:00.220
<v Speaker 2>Es spectacular?

00:03:00.220 --> 00:03:02.459
<v Speaker 1>Almost the same word.

00:03:02.459 --> 00:03:03.660
<v Speaker 2>Oh right.

00:03:03.660 --> 00:03:05.099
<v Speaker 2>Espectacular.

00:03:05.099 --> 00:03:05.580
<v Speaker 2>Good.

00:03:05.580 --> 00:03:09.340
<v Speaker 1>Es espectacular that they begin

00:03:16.319 --> 00:03:17.040
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:03:17.040 --> 00:03:22.319
<v Speaker 1>Es espectacular que comiencen a hablar español.

00:03:22.340 --> 00:03:26.100
<v Speaker 1>It's spectacular that they start to speak Spanish.

00:03:26.100 --> 00:03:32.340
<v Speaker 1>Now after comenzar el empezar you could also put the ing form and the meaning would change a little.

00:03:32.340 --> 00:03:33.940
<v Speaker 1>It would mean it's

00:03:34.240 --> 00:03:37.600
<v Speaker 1>Spectacular that they start out speaking Spanish.

