00:04:19.459 --> 00:04:20.340
<v Speaker 2>Espanyol.

00:04:20.340 --> 00:04:20.659
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:04:20.659 --> 00:04:25.300
<v Speaker 1>And here we don't need the a because we're not connecting to a two form.

00:04:25.300 --> 00:04:30.180
<v Speaker 1>What was the verb to finish or to terminate?

00:04:30.440 --> 00:04:32.360
<v Speaker 2>Hmm Terminar.

00:04:32.360 --> 00:04:33.720
<v Speaker 1>Terminar.

00:04:33.720 --> 00:04:42.120
<v Speaker 1>Now if you want to say a sentence like I want you guys to speak with me when you finish selling them.

00:04:41.860 --> 00:04:44.500
<v Speaker 1>We will say when you finish to sell them.

00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:46.500
<v Speaker 1>Here we won't use the ing.

00:04:46.500 --> 00:04:53.300
<v Speaker 1>But to finish, terminar, is also one of those verbs that needs a preposition to connect.

00:04:53.020 --> 00:04:55.100
<v Speaker 1>to the next two form.

00:04:55.100 --> 00:04:58.060
<v Speaker 1>In this case the preposition is de.

00:04:58.060 --> 00:05:04.380
<v Speaker 1>So to finish selling them is terminar de vender.

00:05:04.320 --> 00:05:09.760
<v Speaker 1>So I want you guys to speak with me when you finish selling them.

00:05:09.760 --> 00:05:13.360
<v Speaker 1>So the first bit is I want you guys to speak with me.

00:05:13.360 --> 00:05:15.280
