00:05:16.520 --> 00:05:20.680
<v Speaker 2>Quiero que hablen conmigo.

00:05:20.680 --> 00:05:21.479
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:05:21.479 --> 00:05:22.680
<v Speaker 1>Mood tense.

00:05:22.680 --> 00:05:25.160
<v Speaker 1>Quiero que hablen conmigo.

00:05:25.160 --> 00:05:25.479
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:05:25.479 --> 00:05:26.680
<v Speaker 1>I want that you.

00:05:27.020 --> 00:05:28.380
<v Speaker 1>talk with me.

00:05:28.380 --> 00:05:33.820
<v Speaker 1>Quiero que hablen conmigo when you finish selling them.

00:05:33.820 --> 00:05:37.660
<v Speaker 1>So when you finish and we're still speaking to you guys

00:05:39.780 --> 00:05:42.020
<v Speaker 2>Quanto terminen?

00:05:42.020 --> 00:05:42.660
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:05:42.820 --> 00:05:44.980
<v Speaker 1>Why did you use the mood tense there?

00:05:44.980 --> 00:05:46.740
<v Speaker 1>Quando terminen?

00:05:48.520 --> 00:05:52.280
<v Speaker 2>Because it's it's the future when Good.

00:05:52.280 --> 00:05:58.600
<v Speaker 1>When quando refers to generally, we won't use the mood tense, we just use the present

00:05:58.539 --> 00:06:03.740
<v Speaker 1>And here referring to a future event that hasn't happened after quando we use the mood tense.

00:06:03.740 --> 00:06:04.860
<v Speaker 1>Well remembered.

00:06:10.379 --> 00:06:12.379
<v Speaker 1>And we're not going to use selling, we're going to use

00:06:12.539 --> 00:06:20.940
<v Speaker 2>Two sell and we connect that with de Quanto termine de venderlo

00:06:23.060 --> 00:06:25.300
<v Speaker 2>Good vendor los.

00:06:25.300 --> 00:06:25.780
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:06:25.780 --> 00:06:32.340
<v Speaker 1>So all together I want you guys to speak with me when you finish selling them

00:06:33.160 --> 00:06:40.760
<v Speaker 2>Quiero que hablen conmigo cuando terminen de venderlos.

00:06:41.260 --> 00:06:45.100
<v Speaker 1>Quiero que hablen conmigo cuando terminen de venderlos.

00:06:45.100 --> 00:06:50.540
<v Speaker 1>So this means I want you guys to speak with me when you finish selling them.

00:06:50.240 --> 00:06:54.080
<v Speaker 1>But terminar we can also use like end up.

00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:58.400
<v Speaker 1>I want you guys to speak with me when you end up selling them

00:06:58.620 --> 00:07:06.860
<v Speaker 1>So using the ing form after terminar instead of the and the two form gives us this meaning of end up

00:07:07.539 --> 00:07:12.500
<v Speaker 1>So if you wanted to say I want you guys to speak with me when you end up selling them.

00:07:12.500 --> 00:07:15.060
<v Speaker 1>So I want you guys to speak with me

00:07:19.080 --> 00:07:21.000
<v Speaker 1>When you end up selling them.

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:26.840
<v Speaker 1>So we will say when you finish and then we will actually use the ING.

00:07:30.840 --> 00:07:31.320
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:39.160
<v Speaker 1>I want you guys to speak with me when you end up selling them.

00:07:39.020 --> 00:07:44.780
<v Speaker 1>So there is a difference here depending on whether we use the two form or the ing form.

00:07:44.780 --> 00:07:53.580
<v Speaker 1>Just as we saw with empezar or comensar, there can be a difference between using the two form afterwards or the ing form afterwards.

00:07:52.860 --> 00:08:06.700
