00:08:06.639 --> 00:08:16.000
<v Speaker 1>If the two form is joining with a preposition, then maybe this particular verb takes the ing form afterwards as well with a slightly different meaning.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:20.639
<v Speaker 1>Empesar a hablar to start to speak, to start speaking

00:08:20.440 --> 00:08:28.360
<v Speaker 1>Empezar hablando to actually begin something speaking or as we would probably say to start out speaking

00:08:28.420 --> 00:08:32.580
<v Speaker 1>Terminar de vender to finish selling.

00:08:32.580 --> 00:08:37.539
<v Speaker 1>Terminar vendiendo to end up selling.

00:08:37.220 --> 00:08:46.180
<v Speaker 1>So what we have aimed to teach here is the idea of the moot tense, the general feeling of the moot tense and the kind of constructions

00:08:46.360 --> 00:08:56.280
<v Speaker 1>in which it occurs and like I said understanding the mood tense is about listening out for it and listening out for how people around you use it.

00:08:56.240 --> 00:09:07.360
